From: Prajw <prajw@trivartatech>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 19:27:54 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?fix:=20CSRF=20419=20=E2=80=94=20read=20token=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?from=20XSRF-TOKEN=20cookie,=20not=20Inertia=20prop?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Bulk reset / create missing / export endpoints were 419'ing because
usePage().props.csrf_token is undefined — HandleInertiaRequests doesn't
share csrf_token as a prop in this app. The fetch calls were sending
'X-CSRF-TOKEN: undefined'.

The pre-existing per-row Reset button had the same bug, just hadn't
been exercised recently.

Now reads the XSRF-TOKEN cookie directly (same source axios uses) and
sends it as X-XSRF-TOKEN. The cookie is rotated by Laravel on session
changes so it's always fresh, unlike the <meta name=csrf-token> tag
which is static once rendered.

Verified in preview: bulk-reset endpoint now returns 401 (auth
required) instead of 419 (CSRF mismatch) when called with the new
header — i.e., the CSRF middleware is now satisfied.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 resources/js/Pages/School/Users/Index.vue | 19 +++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/resources/js/Pages/School/Users/Index.vue b/resources/js/Pages/School/Users/Index.vue
index 1d8e44e..27036d1 100644
--- a/resources/js/Pages/School/Users/Index.vue
+++ b/resources/js/Pages/School/Users/Index.vue
@@ -10,6 +10,17 @@ import { usePermissions } from '@/Composables/usePermissions';
 const toast = useToast();
 const { can } = usePermissions();
 
+// CSRF — Laravel sets the `XSRF-TOKEN` cookie and rotates it on session
+// changes. The meta tag is set once on first render and goes stale on
+// long-lived pages. Reading the cookie + sending as X-XSRF-TOKEN is what
+// axios does automatically; we replicate it here for our fetch() calls.
+const csrfHeader = () => {
+    const m = document.cookie.match(/(?:^|; )XSRF-TOKEN=([^;]+)/);
+    return m
+        ? { 'X-XSRF-TOKEN': decodeURIComponent(m[1]) }
+        : { 'X-CSRF-TOKEN': document.querySelector('meta[name="csrf-token"]')?.getAttribute('content') ?? '' };
+};
+
 const props = defineProps({
     users:           Object,
     filters:         Object,
@@ -73,7 +84,7 @@ const handleResetPassword = async (user) => {
     try {
         const response = await fetch(`/school/users/${user.id}/reset-password`, {
             method: 'POST',
-            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'X-CSRF-TOKEN': usePage().props.csrf_token },
+            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', ...csrfHeader() },
         });
         const result = await response.json();
         if (result.success) {
@@ -119,7 +130,7 @@ const createMissing = async (type) => {
     try {
         const res = await fetch('/school/users/create-missing', {
             method: 'POST',
-            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'X-CSRF-TOKEN': usePage().props.csrf_token },
+            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', ...csrfHeader() },
             body: JSON.stringify({ type }),
         });
         const result = await res.json();
@@ -146,7 +157,7 @@ const bulkReset = async () => {
     try {
         const res = await fetch('/school/users/bulk-reset', {
             method: 'POST',
-            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'X-CSRF-TOKEN': usePage().props.csrf_token },
+            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', ...csrfHeader() },
             body: JSON.stringify({ user_ids: ids }),
         });
         const result = await res.json();
@@ -167,7 +178,7 @@ const exportCredentials = async (format) => {
     if (bulkRows.value.length === 0) return;
     const res = await fetch('/school/users/export-credentials', {
         method: 'POST',
-        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'X-CSRF-TOKEN': usePage().props.csrf_token },
+        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', ...csrfHeader() },
         body: JSON.stringify({ rows: bulkRows.value, format }),
     });
     if (!res.ok) { toast.error('Export failed.'); return; }
